I was speaking in broad terms because the post to which I was responding did so.  My knowledge of the cultural aspects of the middle east is not limited to US-perpetuated stereo-types.  I went to school with many Arab students in Switzerland -- not Arab Americans, but Arabs who were still citizens of their homelands and whose parents served as diplomats from various Middle Eastern countries.  I heard them speak firsthand (sometimes proudly, sometimes disparagingly) of their countrys' lack of social welfare and alacritous use of the death penalty.  <br>
